metadata.description: US Total Nonfarm Employment | Value 03/26 | April 2026 Release

outcome_space.description: US Total Nonfarm Employment (Thousands, Seasonally Adjusted)

base_case.condition: What will the US Total Nonfarm Employment be for {observation.reference_date}?
base_case.fsp_resolution: FSP equals the total number of paid employees working in the United States (in thousands), excluding farm workers, private household employees, and non-profit organization employees, for the month of {observation.reference_date}, as reported by the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics in the Employment Situation report released on {observation.release_date}. Employment values are scaled by 0.001 (e.g., 159,500 thousand employees reported by FRED settles as FSP = 159.500). This data is available via the FRED API (Series ID: PAYEMS).

edge_cases.condition: The U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics announces that it cannot produce the Total Nonfarm Employment number for {observation.reference_date} due to exceptional circumstances (such as government shutdown) but provides an alternative estimate or proxy value.
edge_cases.fsp_resolution: FSP = the alternative estimate or proxy value provided by the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics, scaled by 0.001.

edge_cases.condition: The U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics announces that it cannot produce the Total Nonfarm Employment number for {observation.reference_date} due to exceptional circumstances and will not publish one for this period.
edge_cases.fsp_resolution: FSP = oracle_fallback.fallback_fsp, the most recent Total Nonfarm Employment rate available prior to the scheduled release date of {observation.release_date}.

oracle_config.description: Prototype1 oracle configuration for Total Nonfarm Employment data retrieval from FRED API
